//! Gemma4Pipeline — distributed inference forward pass for Gemma3 / Gemma4
//! IT models on the gnosis Rust mesh. Sibling to `NativeLlamaPipeline`
//! (which handles Qwen2 / LLaMA) — both consume the same `KnotWeights`
//! backend, the same KV cache, and the same `mat_vec_dispatch_batch`
//! kernels. The split lives at the per-layer math level: Gemma uses
//! pre/post-attention RMSNorms, partial-RoPE, GeGLU, sliding-vs-global
//! attention dispatch, and a final tanh logit softcap.
//!
//! This module targets Gemma4-31B-IT first (60 layers, hidden=5376,
//! num_heads=32, num_kv_heads=16, head_dim=256, sliding_window_pattern=6,
//! global_head_dim=512, global_num_kv_heads=4, query_pre_attn_scalar=168,
//! final_logit_softcap=30, rope_partial_factor=0.25, rope_scaling=8.0
//! linear on global, rope_local_base_freq=10000 on sliding,
//! rope_theta=1000000 on global). AltUp/Laurel/PLE are intentionally
//! out of scope (E4B-only — added later).
//!
//! References:
//!   - HF transformers `modeling_gemma3.py` / `modeling_gemma4.py`
//!   - llama.cpp `build_gemma3` / `build_gemma4` (LLM_ARCH_GEMMA3/4)
//!   - apps/edge-workers/src/lib/distributed-inference/gcp-layer-node.ts
//!     (the working TS Aether implementation, lines 2300-2700)

